    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-09T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-09T21:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/812: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-09T23:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 9, 1933—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 10—12:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. My 109, November 8, 9 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs has just telephoned
                    me that he has reached agreement with Minister of Finance and that they request
                    the Department to furnish copy of the plan to Bondholders’ Commission. He
                    expresses the hope that it can be dealt with expeditiously. Foreign Minister
                    asks me to say that Brazilian Government is determined to work in good
                    understanding with the United States.</p>
                <p>This would seem to dispose of the danger of action in the course of the next few
                    days—but it must be borne in mind that we are not dealing in this matter with a
                    highly organized Treasury Department … It is therefore important to get active
                    negotiation started in some form as soon as possible. It would be helpful if
                    Department would furnish me with an indication of the procedure
                    contemplated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
